sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User<br/>Phone or Browser
    participant App as Merchant App<br/>or Website
    participant Wallet as Wallet SDK<br/>PassKit or GPay API
    participant SE as SE or HCE<br/>Credential Store
    participant Server as Merchant<br/>Server
    participant PSP as Payment Processor<br/>Stripe, Adyen, etc.
    participant Network as Card Network<br/>plus TSP
    participant Issuer as Issuing<br/>Bank

    Note over User,Issuer: In-App and Web Payment Flow

    alt In-App Payment
        App->>Wallet: PKPaymentAuthorizationViewController<br/>or PaymentsClient.loadPaymentData
    else Web Payment
        App->>Wallet: Apple Pay JS API<br/>or Google Pay API button click
    end

    Wallet->>User: Display payment sheet<br/>Card, amount, merchant name<br/>OS-controlled -- cannot be spoofed

    User->>SE: Authenticate with biometrics<br/>Face ID, fingerprint, or device PIN
    SE->>SE: Generate cryptogram<br/>using in-app domain keys<br/>DPAN plus one-time token

    SE-->>Wallet: Encrypted payment token
    Wallet-->>App: Return token to callback

    App->>Server: Send encrypted payment token<br/>via HTTPS

    Server->>PSP: Submit token for processing<br/>PSP decrypts if needed
    PSP->>Network: DPAN plus cryptogram<br/>Standard network auth

    Network->>Network: TSP detokenizes DPAN<br/>Validates cryptogram<br/>Checks domain -- in-app

    Network->>Issuer: Auth request with real PAN
    Issuer->>Issuer: Standard authorization<br/>balance, fraud, limits

    Issuer-->>Network: Approved
    Network-->>PSP: Re-tokenized response
    PSP-->>Server: Payment confirmed
    Server-->>App: Order confirmed
    App-->>User: Success screen

    Note over User,Issuer: Merchant server never sees real PAN<br/>Only receives encrypted token
